Hong Kong, China to Add Entry Point for Flights to Mainland

-- B y   J a s m i n e   W a n g
-- 
2011-08-12T11:27:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/hong-kong-china-to-add-entry-point-for-flights-to-mainland.html
Hong Kong  and China will add a third
entry point for flights to the mainland’s airspace starting next
month to ease traffic.  Flights to Shenzhen over Hong Kong will use the new entry
point from September 22, the city’s Civil Aviation Department
said in a statement today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Jasmine Wang in Hong Kong at 
